GBV undermines the health, dignity and security of its victims, yet it remains shrouded in a culture of silence.GBV knows no social, economic or national boundaries. Gender-based violence (GBV) is an immensely rooted issue globally. Both women and men experience it, but the threat significantly increases for women and girls. It’s entrenched in gender inequality, stereotypes, the abuse of power and harmful norms due to lack of discourse.
GBV knows no social, economic or national boundaries. It’s a global pandemic that affects one in three women in their lifetime.



