According to The World Bank Report, September 2019, GBV plagues communities worldwide where 35 per cent of women experience either physical and/or sexual intimate partner violence or non-partner sexual violence.
Globally, seven per cent of women have been sexually assaulted by someone other than a partner, 38 per cent of murders of women are committed by an intimate partner and 200 million women have experienced female genital mutilation.



